Where:

    $W_0$: Base weights (shared across all tasks)

    $U_i, V_i$: Low-rank basis matrices (task-specific directions)

    $\alpha_i(t)$: Learnable functions of time (coefficients)

    $t \in [0,1]$: Position on the manifold

This formulation has several appealing properties:

    Continuity: Smooth interpolation between tasks

    Efficiency: Only $O(k \cdot \text{rank})$ additional parameters

    Geometric interpretation: Tasks live on a low-dimensional manifold

1.3 Contributions

This paper makes the following contributions:

    Empirical demonstration that temporal manifolds can separate, blend, and remember multiple tasks

